(b)

Test verisini kullanarak ortalama hata karesini (test MSE) hesaplaynz. Test verisindeki gerek hedef deiken ile kestirim deerlerinin serpilme grafiini 45-derece dorusu ile birlikte iziniz ve R-kare ile birlikte yorumlaynz.

#Tahmin yapma

# Serpilme grafii izme
library(ggplot2)

  geom_point() +

  labs(title = "Gerek ve Tahmin Edilen Deerlerin Serpilme Grafii",
       x = "Gerek Deerler",
       y = "Tahmin Edilen Deerler") +
  theme_minimal()

# R-kare deerini hesaplama

## [1] "Test Seti R-kare: 0.828000426768596"

(a)

nceki sorulardaki sigorta veri kmesini kullanarak lmaliyet iin Boosting algoritmasn eitmek istiyoruz. Uygun ayarlanma parametrelerini kullanarak GBM paketi ile modeli eitiniz. Test MSE deerini hesaplaynz ve nceki sonularla karlatrnz.

library(gbm)
## Warning: package 'gbm' was built under R version 4.3.3
## Loaded gbm 2.1.9
## This version of gbm is no longer under development. Consider transitioning to gbm3, https://github.com/gbm-developers/gbm3
# Boosting modeli oluturma
set.seed(1)
boost_model <- gbm(lmaliyet ~ yas + cinsiyet + BMI + cocuksay + sigara + bolge, 
                   data = train_data, 
                   distribution = "gaussian", 
                   n.trees = 1000,
                   interaction.depth = 1,
                   shrinkage = 0.2)

# Tahmin yapma
boost_predictions <- predict(boost_model, newdata = test_data, n.trees = 1000)

# MSE hesaplama
boost_mse <- mean((test_data$lmaliyet - boost_predictions)^2)
print(paste("Boosting Modeli Test MSE:", boost_mse))
## [1] "Boosting Modeli Test MSE: 0.192925672145215"

Yorum

Dier modellere gre hata oran yksek olduundan baarszdr.

(b)

GBM boosting algoritmasnda sememiz gereken 3 ayarlanma parametresi vardr. Bu hiperparametreler iin aadaki gibi bir grid oluturalm.

# Hiperparametre gridini oluturma
B <- c(500, 1000, 2000, 5000) # n.trees
d <- c(1, 2, 3, 4)            # interaction.depth
lambda <- c(0.001, 0.01, 0.02, 0.03, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2) # shrinkage
G <- expand.grid(B = B, d = d, lambda = lambda)

Eitim verilerini kullanarak 5-katl apraz geerleme yntemi ile optimal ayarlanma parametrelerini seiniz. Bu deerleri kullanarak test MSEyi hesaplaynz.

# Eitim ve test MSE deerlerini saklamak iin
nG <- nrow(G)
boost_train_MSE <- rep(NA, nG)
boost_test_MSE <- rep(NA, nG)
cv_errors <- rep(NA, nG)

# Boosting modeli eitme ve apraz dorulama ile MSE hesaplama
set.seed(1)
for (i in 1:nG) {
  params <- G[i, ]
  model <- gbm(lmaliyet ~ yas + cinsiyet + BMI + cocuksay + sigara + bolge, 
               data = train_data, 
               distribution = "gaussian", 
               n.trees = params$B, 
               interaction.depth = params$d, 
               shrinkage = params$lambda, 
               cv.folds = 5)
  
  # apraz dorulama hatas
  cv_errors[i] <- min(model$cv.error)
  
  # Test seti MSE
  boost_pred_test <- predict(model, newdata = test_data, n.trees = params$B) 
  boost_test_MSE[i] <- mean((test_data$lmaliyet - boost_pred_test)^2)
  
  # Eitim seti MSE
  boost_pred_train <- predict(model, newdata = train_data, n.trees = params$B) 
  boost_train_MSE[i] <- mean((train_data$lmaliyet - boost_pred_train)^2) 
}

# En iyi parametreleri bulma
best_params <- G[which.min(cv_errors), ]
best_test_MSE <- min(boost_test_MSE)
print(paste("En iyi parametreler: n.trees =", best_params$B, 
            "interaction.depth =", best_params$d, 
            "shrinkage =", best_params$lambda))
## [1] "En iyi parametreler: n.trees = 2000 interaction.depth = 4 shrinkage = 0.05"
print(paste("Boosting Modeli En yi Test MSE:", best_test_MSE))
## [1] "Boosting Modeli En yi Test MSE: 0.127327713784382"

usdret: USD/TL dviz kurundaki gnlk deiim, %.

usddirection: iki seviyeli faktr deikeni, usdretin iaret negatifse Down, pozitifse Up.

usdretlag1-usdretlag5: usdretin 5 gnlk gecikmeli deerleri, birinci gecikme, ikinci gecikme, vs.

bistretlag1-bistretlag5: BIST100 getirilerinin gecikmeli deerleri.

Bugnk dviz kurunun ynn ngrmek isteyen bir yatrmcnn son be gnlk dviz kuru ve BIST100 hareketlerini bildiini varsayyoruz.

Verileri aadaki gibi eitim ve test kmelerine ayralm:

fin_train <- finmarkets |> filter(year<=2016)
fin_test <- finmarkets |> filter(year>2016)

(b)

Hedef deiken mutluluk iin bir LASSO regresyon modeli tahmin ediniz. Ayarlanma parametresi lambdaya 5-katl apraz geerleme ile belirleyiniz. Hangi deikenler seildi?

library(glmnet)
## Warning: package 'glmnet' was built under R version 4.3.3
## Loading required package: Matrix
## Warning: package 'Matrix' was built under R version 4.3.3
## 
## Attaching package: 'Matrix'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:tidyr':
## 
##     expand, pack, unpack
## Loaded glmnet 4.1-8
# Hedef deiken (mutluluk)
y <- veriler$mutluluk

# Bamsz deikenler
X <- veriler %>%
  select(-mutluluk, -il) %>% # `mutluluk` ve `il` deikenlerini karyoruz
  as.matrix()

# LASSO modeli ve 5-katl apraz dorulama
set.seed(123)
cv_lasso <- cv.glmnet(X, y, alpha = 1, nfolds = 5)

# apraz dorulama sonularn grselletirme
plot(cv_lasso)

# En iyi lambda deerini bulma (one standard error rule)
best_lambda <- cv_lasso$lambda.1se
print("LASSO CV en iyi lambda deeri (one standard error):")
## [1] "LASSO CV en iyi lambda deeri (one standard error):"
print(best_lambda)
## [1] 0.830201
# En iyi lambda deeriyle LASSO modelini eitme
lasso_model <- glmnet(X, y, alpha = 1)

# Seilen deikenlerin isimlerini belirleme
lasso_coefficients <- predict(lasso_model, type = "coefficients", s = best_lambda)
lasso_coefficients <- as.matrix(lasso_coefficients) # Matris olarak dntr
selected_features <- lasso_coefficients[-1, ] #(intercept)
selected_feature_names <- rownames(lasso_coefficients)[which(selected_features != 0)]

# Seilen deikenleri yazdrma
print("Seilen deikenler:")
## [1] "Seilen deikenler:"
print(selected_feature_names)
## [1] "ev_kalite"        "doktor_basv"      "atik_hiz"         "gurultu_kir"     
## [5] "bel_temiz_tatmin" "tra_kaza"         "avm"
